<exercise>
<statement><p>
Imagine that the vector field <m>\vv(x,y) = x\,\hi+y\,\hj</m>
</p>

<p>is the velocity field of a moving fluid.
<ol marker="a">
<li>
At time <m>0</m> you drop a twig into the fluid at
the point <m>(1,1)</m>. What is the approximate position of the twig
at time <m>t=0.01</m>?
</li>
<li>
At time <m>0</m> you drop a twig into the fluid at
the point <m>(0,0)</m>. What is the position of the twig
at time <m>t=0.01</m>?
</li>
<li>
At time <m>0</m> you drop a twig into the fluid at
the point <m>(0,0)</m>. What is the position of the twig
at time <m>t=10</m>?
</li>
</ol>
</p></statement>

<hint><p>
When the twig is at <m>(x,y)</m> it has velocity <m>\vv(x,y)</m>.
</p></hint>

<answer><p>
(a) <m>(1.01\,,\,1.01)</m></p><p>
(b) <m>(0\,,\,0)</m></p><p>
(c) <m>(0\,,\,0)</m>
</p></answer>

<solution><p>
(a)
At time <m>0</m> the velocity of the twig is
<m>\vv(1,1) =\hi+\hj</m>. So at time <m>t=0.01</m>, the position of the
twig is approximately
<me>
(1,1) + 0.01(1,1) = (1.01\,,\,1.01)
</me>
</p>

<p>(b)
At time <m>0</m> the velocity of the twig is
<m>\vv(0,0) =\vZero</m>. So at time <m>t=0.01</m>, the position of the
twig is
<me>
(0,0) + 0.01(0,0) = (0\,,\,0)
</me>
</p>

<p>(c) At time <m>0</m> the velocity of the twig is <m>\vv(0,0) =\vZero</m>.
So it is stationary and its velocity remains zero for all time.
The position of the twig at time <m>10</m>, and in fact at all times,
is <m>(0\,,\,0)</m>.
</p>

</solution>
</exercise>

<exercise>
<statement><p>
Imagine that the vector field <m>\vv(x,y) = 2x\,\hi -\hj</m>
</p>

<p>is the velocity field of a moving fluid.
At time <m>0</m> you drop a twig into the fluid at
the point <m>(0,0)</m>. What is the position of the twig
at time <m>t=10</m>?
</p></statement>

<hint><p>
Whenever the twig is on the <m>y</m>-axis, its velocity is parallel to the <m>y</m>-axis.
So it remains on the <m>y</m>-axis for all time.
</p></hint>

<answer><p>
<m>(0\,,\,-10)</m>
</p></answer>

<solution><p>
The velocity of the fluid at all points of the <m>y</m>-axis
is <m>-\hj</m>. So the twig will remain on the <m>y</m>-axis and will
consequently have velocity <m>-\hj</m> for all time. The position
of the twig at time <m>10</m> will be
<me>
(0,0)+10(0,-1) = (0\,,\,-10)
</me>
</p></solution>
</exercise>
</exercisegroup>

