<p>The frame is lifted from the centre of the circle. The edges of the frame drag on the ground, keeping the frame in the shape of a right circular cone that is becoming taller and thinner.
</p>

<sidebyside widths="48% 20%" valign="middle">
<image><latex-image>\begin{tikzpicture}
\draw (0,0) node[vertex]{};
\filldraw[fill opacity=0.2] (0,0)--(-2,-1) arc(180:360:2cm and .75cm)--(0,0);
